This paper deals with resource allocation in LTE networks with D2D support, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI) and information theory (IT). The paper also proposes algorithms to solve the problem, which falls under the category of systems and control (SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of D2D mode on content delivery, which is related to multimedia (MM) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (DC).
